comments: Giddey (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
At the end of the drive, Reaves (LAL) places his arm on Dort's (OKC) front and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Dort (OKC) extends his arm out on his contest and incidental contact occurs with Anthony's (LAL) hand after the release on the jump shot attempt.
Anthony (LAL) briefly grasps Favors' (OKC) jersey as they jostle for potential rebounding position. The contact is marginal and the shot is made.
Giddey (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Anthony (LAL).
Anthony (LAL) briefly grasps Giddey's (OKC) jersey during his shot at the basket and the contact is marginal as it does not affect Giddey's ability to legally contest the shot.
Anthony (LAL) and Favors (OKC) reach for the ball and incidental contact occurs as they come together during the rebound.

After Reaves (LAL) initially makes contact with the ball on his block attempt, his hand slides off the ball and onto Dort's (OKC) arm while Dort is still in full control and possession. The contact affects his shot attempt at the basket.
During the screen, Bazley (OKC) and Anthony (LAL) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in Bazley's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs with his slightly extended arm as Bazley goes under the screen.
Reaves (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Dort (OKC).
Favors (OKC) makes clean ball contact as he tries to grab the rebound away from Davis (LAL).

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Westbrook (LAL) loses control of the ball on his gather and throws an errant pass out of bounds.
Williams (OKC) makes incidental foot to foot contact with his teammate Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC), which causes him to stumble during the inbound.

Westbrook (LAL) never fully establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not give Williams the time and distance to avoid the contact on the pick. The contact caused by Westbrook affects Williams' ability to contest the jump shot by Anthony (LAL).
Davis (LAL) moves into and makes contact with Dort's (OKC) body, which affects his SQBR.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Williams' (OKC) path and is not wide when incidental foot to foot contact occurs on the screen.
Favors (OKC) makes clean ball contact as he tries to dislodge the rebound from Davis (LAL) and then removes his arm to avoid contact with Davis' arm on his putback shot attempt.
